goals.question: What is the average wheat production and wages per year?

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]

    plt.plot(data['year'], data['wheat'], label='Wheat Production', color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Wheat Production (tons)')
    plt.title('What is the trend in wheat production over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['wheat'], data['wages'])
    plt.xlabel('Wheat Production (tons)')
    plt.ylabel('Wages (USD)')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between wheat production and wages?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['wheat'], bins=10, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Wheat Production')
    plt.axvline(data['wheat'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['wheat'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Wheat Production (tons)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wheat production?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]

    fig, ax1 = plt.subplots()
    ax2 = ax1.twinx()

    ax1.bar(data['year'], data['wheat'], color='b', label='Wheat Production')
    ax2.plot(data['year'], data['wages'], color='r', label='Wages')

    ax1.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax1.set_ylabel('Wheat Production (tons)', color='b')
    ax2.set_ylabel('Wages (USD)', color='r')

    ax1.tick_params(axis='y', labelcolor='b')
    ax2.tick_params(axis='y', labelcolor='r')

    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the average wheat production and wages per year?', wrap=True)

    fig.legend(loc='upper left', bbox_to_anchor=(0.1, 0.9))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
